# Regression: error branch.
# `CREATE POLICY ON foo::bar` where neither `foo::bar` nor `foo` resolves to an
# existing namespace must fail loudly. Prior bug: the planner silently fell
# into the "specific shape" branch and stored (target_namespace=foo,
# target_shape=bar). That policy never matched any real shape, so reads in
# inject_from_policies hit the default-deny branch, injected Filter(false),
# and returned silent empty results. Subscribe was unaffected because
# subscription compilation skips inject_from_policies.

!admin 'CREATE TABLE POLICY p ON foo::bar { from: { filter { true } } }'
---
> Error CA_002
>   namespace `foo::bar` not found
>
> LOCATION
>   line 1, column 26
>
> RQL
>   1 │ CREATE TABLE POLICY p ON foo::bar { from: { filter { true } } }
>     │                          ~~~~~~~~
>     │
>     │                 unknown namespace reference
>
> HELP
>   make sure the namespace exists before using it or create it first
>

# Parent exists but full path does not: still must error, since `bar` is
# neither a namespace nor a real shape inside `foo` at policy-creation time.
(admin 'CREATE NAMESPACE foo')
!admin 'CREATE TABLE POLICY p ON foo::missing::deeper { from: { filter { true } } }'
---
> Error CA_002
>   namespace `foo::missing::deeper` not found
>
> LOCATION
>   line 1, column 26
>
> RQL
>   1 │ CREATE TABLE POLICY p ON foo::missing::deeper { from: { filter { true } } }
>     │                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
>     │
>     │                       unknown namespace reference
>
> HELP
>   make sure the namespace exists before using it or create it first
>
